-SL1500-e1755778160670-50x37.jpg.webp 50w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/812NKObZyZL-AC-SL1500-e1755778160670-75x56.jpg.webp 75w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/812NKObZyZL-AC-SL1500-e1755778160670-100x74.jpg.webp 100w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/812NKObZyZL-AC-SL1500-e1755778160670-200x149.jpg.webp 200w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/812NKObZyZL-AC-SL1500-e1755778160670-500x371.jpg.webp 500w" sizes="(max-width: 1488px) 100vw, 1488px" />
Batteria, ricarica e prestazioni
Uno dei punti di forza di questo modello è la maggiore autonomia: 30 ore per la versione da 41mm e 40 per quella da 45mm in condizioni standard, che diventano 48 e 72 ore rispettivamente attivando il Battery Saver. Migliorata anche la velocità di ricarica: bastano 15 minuti per arrivare al 50%, un progresso notevole rispetto alla generazione passata. Il merito, probabilmente, è anche del processore Snapdragon W5 Gen 2 di Qualcomm che oltre ad assicurare maggiore fluidità e reattività, offre una migliore efficienza energetica.
<img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1425110" title="Pixel Watch 4 è lo smartwatch che si ricarica in 15 minuti e manda messaggi anche dallo spazio - macitynet.it" src="https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/718uR-c7gbL-AC-SL1500.jpg.webp" alt="Pixel Watch 4 è lo smartwatch che si ricarica in 15 minuti e manda messaggi anche dallo spazio - macitynet.it" width="1376" height="1500" srcset="https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/718uR-c7gbL-AC-SL1500.jpg.webp 1376w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/718uR-c7gbL-AC-SL1500-440x480.jpg.webp 440w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/718uR-c7gbL-AC-SL1500-1101x1200.jpg.webp 1101w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/718uR-c7gbL-AC-SL1500-385x420.jpg.webp 385w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/718uR-c7gbL-AC-SL1500-696x759.jpg.webp 696w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/718uR-c7gbL-AC-SL1500-1068x1164.jpg.webp 1068w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/718uR-c7gbL-AC-SL1500-46x50.jpg.webp 46w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/718uR-c7gbL-AC-SL1500-69x75.jpg.webp 69w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/718uR-c7gbL-AC-SL1500-92x100.jpg.webp 92w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/718uR-c7gbL-AC-SL1500-183x200.jpg.webp 183w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/718uR-c7gbL-AC-SL1500-459x500.jpg.webp 459w" sizes="(max-width: 1376px) 100vw, 1376px" />
Funzionalità avanzate
La grande novità è l’introduzione del supporto alla comunicazione satellitare: il Pixel Watch 4 è il primo smartwatch al mondo a integrare una soluzione standard basata su satellite, grazie alla collaborazione con Skylo e alle nuove piattaforme Qualcomm. Questo permette di inviare messaggi di emergenza anche senza smartphone o connessione cellulare, ampliando la sicurezza e l’affidabilità in situazioni critiche – un cambiamento rivoluzionario per la categoria.
<img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1425111" title="Pixel Watch 4 è lo smartwatch che si ricarica in 15 minuti e manda messaggi anche dallo spazio - macitynet.it" src="https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/81FvhUcD8LL-AC-SL1500.jpg.webp" alt="Pixel Watch 4 è lo smartwatch che si ricarica in 15 minuti e manda messaggi anche dallo spazio - macitynet.it" width="1500" height="1500" srcset="https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/81FvhUcD8LL-AC-SL1500.jpg.webp 1500w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/81FvhUcD8LL-AC-SL1500-480x480.jpg.webp 480w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/81FvhUcD8LL-AC-SL1500-1200x1200.jpg.webp 1200w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/81FvhUcD8LL-AC-SL1500-360x360.jpg.webp 360w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/81FvhUcD8LL-AC-SL1500-420x420.jpg.webp 420w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/81FvhUcD8LL-AC-SL1500-696x696.jpg.webp 696w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/81FvhUcD8LL-AC-SL1500-1068x1068.jpg.webp 1068w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/81FvhUcD8LL-AC-SL1500-50x50.jpg.webp 50w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/81FvhUcD8LL-AC-SL1500-75x75.jpg.webp 75w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/81FvhUcD8LL-AC-SL1500-100x100.jpg.webp 100w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/81FvhUcD8LL-AC-SL1500-200x200.jpg.webp 200w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/81FvhUcD8LL-AC-SL1500-500x500.jpg.webp 500w" sizes="(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px" />
Non manca, naturalmente, attenzione al lato sport e benessere che resta fortemente affidato all’ecosistema Fitbit. Ritroviamo le classiche funzioni di monitoraggio continuo del battito cardiaco, della SpO2, del sonno, dello stress e dei workout, insieme alle misurazioni ECG, notifiche di aritmia, rilevamento cadute e SOS. Non ci sono nuovi sensori rivoluzionari rispetto al passato, ma l’algoritmo di tracciamento del sonno e il GPS – assicura Google – sono stati migliorati, offrendo dati ancora più precisi per chi pratica running, ciclismo o escursionismo.
<img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1425112" title="Pixel Watch 4 è lo smartwatch che si ricarica in 15 minuti e manda messaggi anche dallo spazio - macitynet.it" src="https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/71rfXNJpUvL-AC-SL1500.jpg.webp" alt="Pixel Watch 4 è lo smartwatch che si ricarica in 15 minuti e manda messaggi anche dallo spazio - macitynet.it" width="1500" height="1500" srcset="https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/71rfXNJpUvL-AC-SL1500.jpg.webp 1500w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/71rfXNJpUvL-AC-SL1500-480x480.jpg.webp 480w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/71rfXNJpUvL-AC-SL1500-1200x1200.jpg.webp 1200w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/71rfXNJpUvL-AC-SL1500-360x360.jpg.webp 360w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/71rfXNJpUvL-AC-SL1500-420x420.jpg.webp 420w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/71rfXNJpUvL-AC-SL1500-696x696.jpg.webp 696w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/71rfXNJpUvL-AC-SL1500-1068x1068.jpg.webp 1068w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/71rfXNJpUvL-AC-SL1500-50x50.jpg.webp 50w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/71rfXNJpUvL-AC-SL1500-75x75.jpg.webp 75w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/71rfXNJpUvL-AC-SL1500-100x100.jpg.webp 100w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/71rfXNJpUvL-AC-SL1500-200x200.jpg.webp 200w,  https://www.macitynet.it/wp-content/webp-express/webp-images/uploads/2025/08/71rfXNJpUvL-AC-SL1500-500x500.jpg.webp 500w" sizes="(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px" />
L’integrazione con Google Gemini è pubblicizzata come la migliore di sempre su un wearable, favorendo l’uso dell’assistente AI direttamente dall’orologio.
Il prezzo per la versione Wifi 41 mm parte da 399 euro, che diventano 499 per la variante LTE. Si preordinano già su Amazon a partire da questo indirizzo. Per la variante più grande da 45 mm si parte da 449 euro.
